sections.markdown: # Adding new fields with additional trigonometric calculations

sections.title: Adding new fields with additional calculations

input.value:
fetch logs //, scanLimitGBytes: 500, samplingRatio: 1000
| sort timestamp desc
| filter matchesValue(log.source, "opentelemetry-iot-dump1090-collector") // Filter logs ingested from the opentelemetry collector for dump1090 from the IOT device
| parse content, "JSON:json_content"
| fieldsAdd aircraft=json_content[aircraft]
| expand aircraft
| fieldsFlatten aircraft
| filter isNotNull(aircraft.lon)
// Set mylat and mylong of the location of the point. Here in this case, this is the lat/long of the airport
| fieldsAdd mylat =-37.882720
| fieldsAdd mylong =145.175580 
| filter isNotNull(aircraft.flight)
// Convert the airport degrees lat/lon to Radians
| fieldsAdd myLatRad = toDouble(degreeToRadian(mylat))
| fieldsAdd myLongRad = toDouble(degreeToRadian(mylong))

// Convert the aircraft's degrees lat/lon to Radians
| fieldsAdd aircraft.lat2rad = toDouble(degreeToRadian(todouble(aircraft.lat)))
| fieldsAdd aircraft.lon2rad = toDouble(degreeToRadian(todouble(aircraft.lon)))


| fieldsAdd dLat = toDouble(aircraft.lat2rad - myLatRad)
| fieldsAdd dLong = toDouble(aircraft.lon2rad - myLongRad)

| fieldsAdd earthRadius = toDouble(6378137) // Earth's radius in meters

// Haversine formula calculates the distance between two points on the Earth's surface given their latitude and longitude.
| fieldsAdd a = sin(toDouble(dLat) / 2) * sin(toDouble(dLat) / 2) + cos(toDouble(myLatRad)) * cos(toDouble(aircraft.lat2rad)) * sin(toDouble(dLong)/2) * sin(toDouble(dLong) /2)
| fieldsAdd C = 2 * atan2(sqrt(a), sqrt(1-a))
| fieldsAdd distance = (earthRadius * C)/1000
| fields timestamp, aircraft.hex, aircraft.flight, aircraft.lat,aircraft.lat2rad, aircraft.lon,aircraft.lon2rad, distance, myLatRad, myLongRad,aircraft.altitude

sections.title: Flights tracked over the past 7 days

input.value:
fetch logs, from:now() - 7d
| filter matchesValue(log.source, "opentelemetry-iot-dump1090-collector") // Filter logs ingested from the opentelemetry collector for dump1090 from the IOT device
| parse content, "JSON:json_content"
| fieldsAdd aircraft=json_content[aircraft]
| expand aircraft
| fieldsFlatten aircraft
| filter isNotNull(aircraft.flight)
| filter isNotNull(aircraft.altitude)
| filterOut aircraft.altitude == "ground"
| fields aircraft.flight, timestamp
| summarize no_of_flights = countDistinct(aircraft.flight), by:{bin(timestamp, 1d), alias:timestamp}
| fields timeframe = timeframe(from:timestamp-1d, to:timestamp),no_of_flights = no_of_flights
| fields timeframe, `TotalFlightsTracked`= no_of_flights
